	<body>
		<outline text="August 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="august2021" >
			<outline text="August 19" type="calendarDay" name="19" >
				<outline text="Hah @elonmusk is already 31 minutes late. Just like Full Self Driving. ;-)

&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j0z4FweCy4M&amp;feature=youtu.be&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 00:32:53 GMT" tweetId="1428515345787097091" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1428515345787097091" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Will be interesting to see the AI knowledge that gets laid down by @elonmusk and team. I am watching. Starts in 20 minutes. Elon is never on time, though. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/wholemarsblog/status/1428501747895439365&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 23:41:32 GMT" tweetId="1428502422255673349" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1428502422255673349" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Official @tesla link: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j0z4FweCy4M&amp;feature=youtu.be&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 00:11:29 GMT" tweetId="1428509959944241156" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1428509959944241156" inReplyToId="1428502422255673349" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="I predicted a clear iPhone. 

At least Apple had a patent for such a thing.

I also thought I would wear Google Glass forever.

And that social media would greatly improve the world.

Sigh. Someday! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/btaylor/status/1428102259523555332&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 23:28:47 GMT" tweetId="1428499214967865356" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1428499214967865356" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Just another Silicon Valley morning. Following “Skype.” :-) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Scobleizer/status/1428416012458741763/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 17:58:10 GMT" tweetId="1428416012458741763" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1428416012458741763" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Dogfooding, we call it. Using your own technology before everyone else sees the need. Very smart for industry pioneers to do. Will help find bugs and opportunities/needs. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brunolarvol/status/1428410190127325201&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 17:42:09 GMT" tweetId="1428411978939203588" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1428411978939203588" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="All you have to do is look at the reactions to Facebook's new Horizons for work and you will see the hate for VR and for Facebook oozing out: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.techmeme.com/210819/p10#a210819p10&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

Can Facebook fix this? No. Can Apple? Yes. Will it? We will see over the next year. I'm bullish still." type="tweet" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 15:50:02 GMT" tweetId="1428383765508677635" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1428383765508677635" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Apple has Ted Lasso and Dolby Atmos music. Facebook has VR for work. I know which one will win. I sold VHS vs. Beta VCRs in the 1980s. Content won there. Content will win here." type="tweet" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 15:51:59 GMT" tweetId="1428384257668382726" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1428384257668382726" inReplyToId="1428383765508677635" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 17" type="calendarDay" name="17" >
				<outline text="I can see lots of meetups in fields ahead. 

Multiplayer gaming will be fun! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/rtovr/status/1427608736944869420&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 17 Aug 2021 21:39:20 GMT" tweetId="1427746895959523329" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1427746895959523329" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 15" type="calendarDay" name="15" >
				<outline text="When I visited the Bush White House I got in an argument with the staff about things they were doing in reaction to 9/11. Their answer:

“It is our job to keep you safe.”

Today we see just how much bullshit that is. 

Wars and spying on people aren’t good answers." type="tweet" created="Sun, 15 Aug 2021 20:40:33 GMT" tweetId="1427007324300877830" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1427007324300877830" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 12" type="calendarDay" name="12" >
				<outline text="If you are in Silicon Valley look outside. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Scobleizer/status/1426010417428459523/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 13 Aug 2021 02:39:12 GMT" tweetId="1426010417428459523" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1426010417428459523" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Extremely smart! Playing now with my kids. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jwegener/status/1425906339390185473&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 12 Aug 2021 22:16:38 GMT" tweetId="1425944341961347078" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425944341961347078" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 11" type="calendarDay" name="11" >
				<outline text="My Tesla sounds better too. Apple is definitely improving Audio in iOS 15 developer betas. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425549403528384512&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 22:29:31 GMT" tweetId="1425585198129762305" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425585198129762305" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Apple is doing some Bluetooth magic to push multi-channel audio to my Tesla." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 22:47:28 GMT" tweetId="1425589712652177414" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425589712652177414" inReplyToId="1425585198129762305" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
						<outline text="On songs like this it isn’t even close. Has better bass, way better, and multi channel plus better fidelity everywhere. Doing A/B tests with Spotify, and Tesla service." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 23:10:19 GMT" tweetId="1425595462220869637" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425595462220869637" inReplyToId="1425589712652177414" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
							<outline text="Sorry here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/us/album/having-our-way-feat-drake/1572789904?i=1572790276&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 23:13:18 GMT" tweetId="1425596214494466048" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425596214494466048" inReplyToId="1425595462220869637" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="iOS developer beta 5, shipped yesterday, makes Dolby Atmos content sound amazing in Apple’s Max and Pro headphones.

Anyone else notice the difference in the audio rendering engine?

Thousands of Dolby Atmos songs: &lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/dolby-atmos-and-spatial-audio/pl.u-E2VCa2qY2A&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 20:07:17 GMT" tweetId="1425549403528384512" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425549403528384512" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="I have only tested them on iPhone 12 Pro Max." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 20:19:17 GMT" tweetId="1425552420709437441" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425552420709437441" inReplyToId="1425549403528384512" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					<outline text="My favorite Atmos recording is from @boxrZhu &lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/us/album/z-train/1579973738?i=1579973746&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 20:27:15 GMT" tweetId="1425554428640120835" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425554428640120835" inReplyToId="1425549403528384512" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					<outline text="My favorite Atmos recording is from @zhumusic

Shipped a few days ago: &lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/us/album/z-train/1579973738?i=1579973746&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 20:32:14 GMT" tweetId="1425555682166673416" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425555682166673416" inReplyToId="1425549403528384512" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 10" type="calendarDay" name="10" >
				<outline text="I once asked astronaut @Astro_Cady to tell me a story I wouldn’t have heard about being in space on TV.

She told me she was stuck for months in the Space Station with an asshole.

The Russians had stuck the American crew with their worst astronaut. 

The rest of the story…" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 19:48:27 GMT" tweetId="1425182272848683009" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425182272848683009" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="The Space Station is very small, she told me, and it was impossible to avoid the guy. 

Being a toxic asshole myself I can imagine the shit she had to put up with.

“How did you handle it?” I asked her." type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 19:48:27 GMT" tweetId="1425182273867943936" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425182273867943936" inReplyToId="1425182272848683009" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
						<outline text="“I focused on the job and remembered the resources the country had spent to put me there.”

I am watching “For All Mankind,” which details the kind of shit women have to deal with every day. 

I am sorry for adding onto the pile of shit." type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 19:48:27 GMT" tweetId="1425182274853564416" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425182274853564416" inReplyToId="1425182273867943936" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
							<outline text="If you ask yourself if a woman deserves to be where she is, you are the problem. Not her. 

She had to be better than you just to get there.

I wish I could go back and tell this to my younger self." type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 19:48:27 GMT" tweetId="1425182275843497985" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1425182275843497985" inReplyToId="1425182274853564416" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 8" type="calendarDay" name="08" >
				<outline text="Will has been a great member of the VR/AR community and needs our help. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/aeonixaeon/status/1424513593236762626&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 08 Aug 2021 23:45:11 GMT" tweetId="1424517075746181120" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1424517075746181120" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="The average music video I see on Apple Music TV has dozens of people who built it.

The least hyped talent is that of team building.

Is the day of the independent contributor over?

VR for mainstream use is even tougher than creating a music video.

&lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/us/station/apple-music-tv/ra.1534941676&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 08 Aug 2021 19:48:34 GMT" tweetId="1424457526603501570" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1424457526603501570" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 7" type="calendarDay" name="07" >
				<outline text="I used 1.4 terabytes of data last month says Comcast.

4K TV sure uses a lot. 

Or maybe my son is doing something whacky in @Roblox.

Either way that is nuts." type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 23:49:52 GMT" tweetId="1424155863594504197" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1424155863594504197" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 5" type="calendarDay" name="05" >
				<outline text="I built a house to celebrate all media. 

Kanye’s life show is amazing! &lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/us/station/apple-music-tv/ra.1534941676&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/zlgqXozJeg" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 03:32:55 GMT" tweetId="1423487221072490497" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423487221072490497" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Plus next year’s Apple product was partially built here." type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 03:34:11 GMT" tweetId="1423487542662361090" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423487542662361090" inReplyToId="1423487221072490497" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					<outline text="There is a story on the walls: there are polygons (the future of media), pixels (the past), and hexagons (how cell networks and autonomous vehicles see the world). Plus an analog painting to represent the real world.

Designed for @Aidan_Wolf. He will augment it all." type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 04:03:40 GMT" tweetId="1423494960393768960" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423494960393768960" inReplyToId="1423487221072490497" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Kanye Live: &lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/us/station/apple-music-tv/ra.1534941676&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 02:54:38 GMT" tweetId="1423477586273792012" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423477586273792012" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Here is a guide to the new icons on Apple Music, made after thousands of listening hours: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/posts/scobleizer_you-might-be-noticing-these-new-icons-showing-activity-6829174957503864832-eVic&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/ZipbMFntwN" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 22:38:23 GMT" tweetId="1423413100343042048" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423413100343042048" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Apple Spatial Audio decoded:

“Lossless:” way better bass.
“High-Res Lossless:” requires better gear and ears than I own.
“Dolby Atmos:” surround sound (best for my gear and ears).
“Spatial Audio (today):” Sound is locked to your TV.
“SA (future):” sound locked to real world." type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 19:12:28 GMT" tweetId="1423361281713598466" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423361281713598466" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="No matter how you look at it Apple Music is way better than Spotify." type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 19:18:25 GMT" tweetId="1423362775942717441" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423362775942717441" inReplyToId="1423361281713598466" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Old habits die hard. Who calls their surround sound system a “stereo” still? I do." type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 18:32:55 GMT" tweetId="1423351328126820354" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423351328126820354" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="The world needs more of this. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/maxn0ir/status/1423307822155116546&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 17:14:57 GMT" tweetId="1423331706904342530" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423331706904342530" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 4" type="calendarDay" name="04" >
				<outline text="Every day we see new AR experiences. 

This one shows you tornado information if you are aiming your phone at a storm.

I dream of stuff like this in glasses and thinking of the lives this could save make me happy.

&lt;a href=&quot;https://collectiveweather.com/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 00:20:23 GMT" tweetId="1423076380854480899" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423076380854480899" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="This will become clearer and clearer over the next year.

Already my Apple Max headphones sound better than when I bought them.

A major paradigm shift is coming to music, movies, TV, games, and other experiences including shopping. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/anastasiadevana/status/1423024960470233089&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 23:23:09 GMT" tweetId="1423061976968617984" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1423061976968617984" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 2" type="calendarDay" name="02" >
				<outline text="This is what I think of when people say “Metaverse.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/terry_wakefield/status/1422285491727122438&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 19:58:28 GMT" tweetId="1422285692084752386" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422285692084752386" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Cofounder of Pixar. Interesting read about computer graphics history. Highly recommended. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/alvyray/status/1415910572118343680&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 19:32:57 GMT" tweetId="1422279272379518987" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422279272379518987" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Fast Company’s review: &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/fastcompany/status/1422210706707996672&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 19:34:38 GMT" tweetId="1422279696285241351" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422279696285241351" inReplyToId="1422279272379518987" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Ever since Andrew Keen @ajkeen gave me heck, in his book, for not knowing my neighbors I make it a point to talk to everyone.

One of the best bagpipers in the world lives on my street.

True story. 

The lady next door studies literature at a high level.

I am the stupid one." type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 08:29:54 GMT" tweetId="1422112407363543041" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422112407363543041" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Andrew: thanks for the gift of knowing my neighbors." type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 08:31:48 GMT" tweetId="1422112886734786564" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422112886734786564" inReplyToId="1422112407363543041" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					<outline text="Oh, across the street? Concrete contractors. Next to a guy who does IPO’s for tech companies." type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 08:39:27 GMT" tweetId="1422114813442805760" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422114813442805760" inReplyToId="1422112407363543041" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Wow. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jimmygunawanapp/status/1422103328679358464&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 07:57:37 GMT" tweetId="1422104284653449221" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422104284653449221" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="The reason there is so much consternation in the VR industry?

TV is turning more amazing for me every week.

After getting a decent 83-inch TV and audio system VR just isn’t nearly as interesting.

We are playing for next year and we are tired of waiting. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Scobleizer/status/1422103112077090821/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 07:52:57 GMT" tweetId="1422103112077090821" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422103112077090821" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="VR is not dead. It just needed more time in the oven." type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 07:53:50 GMT" tweetId="1422103332898762755" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422103332898762755" inReplyToId="1422103112077090821" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					<outline text="I am seeing things in my photography that I never would see without such a big TV. Wow." type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 07:55:05 GMT" tweetId="1422103646590828544" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422103646590828544" inReplyToId="1422103112077090821" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
						<outline text="And VR didn’t show this to me. So sad." type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 07:55:56 GMT" tweetId="1422103861263667205" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422103861263667205" inReplyToId="1422103646590828544" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
						</outline>
					<outline text="Field of view on the TV? More than a HoloLens." type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 08:08:05 GMT" tweetId="1422106918961643520" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422106918961643520" inReplyToId="1422103112077090821" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					<outline text="There are a ton of lessons about the future of the home there. If you have a great OLED 4K TV." type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 08:09:25 GMT" tweetId="1422107252048031744" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422107252048031744" inReplyToId="1422103112077090821" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					<outline text="And I disagree about 8K. OLED beats it big time. A 4K Sony shows my photos better than an 8K Samsung." type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 08:17:35 GMT" tweetId="1422109307936538626" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422109307936538626" inReplyToId="1422103112077090821" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
						<outline text="But I would be very happy if the Samsung was on my wall instead." type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 08:21:13 GMT" tweetId="1422110222676467714" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1422110222676467714" inReplyToId="1422109307936538626" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 31" type="calendarDay" name="31" >
				<outline text="Just went to the Tesla factory in Fremont. Model Y’s are sold out until December. 

Factory employee parking lots are packed. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Scobleizer/status/1421664629445447680/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 02:50:35 GMT" tweetId="1421664629445447680" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1421664629445447680" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Dolby Atmos Music playlists:

You might not realize that Apple Music is dramatically better now than Spotify or Tidal, particularly because Apple now is distributing music in Dolby Atmos format (better bass, better definition, and multi-channel -- much more like the real thing)." type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 17:14:19 GMT" tweetId="1421519605462278144" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1421519605462278144" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="My playlists ONLY include Dolby Atmos music. Others, that say they are for Spatial Audio, include non-Atmos music. Mine aren't yet complete, but get better every day.
Got anything to add?
Good selection: &lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/.../dolby-atmos.../pl.u-E2VCa2qY2A&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; 
Classical Albums: https://t.co/XTmHsikV25" type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 17:14:19 GMT" tweetId="1421519606389252096" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1421519606389252096" inReplyToId="1421519605462278144" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
						<outline text="Popular Music: &lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/.../spatial-audio.../pl.u-ELWFa2qY2A&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;
I'll be working on Jazz this weekend. 
I love following other music lovers too, so your listening behavior brings me more music. So, if you are open to that, let me know your Apple Music profile." type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 17:14:19 GMT" tweetId="1421519607433551875" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1421519607433551875" inReplyToId="1421519606389252096" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
						</outline>
					<outline text="Some people are having trouble with my links. They are all on my profile at &lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/profile/scobleizer&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 17:31:28 GMT" tweetId="1421523923720495104" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1421523923720495104" inReplyToId="1421519605462278144" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 30" type="calendarDay" name="30" >
				<outline text="Do you have a Dolby Atmos audio system?" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 23:41:36 GMT" tweetId="1421254681452421120" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1421254681452421120" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Innovation.
Creativity.
State of the art (best enjoyed on a Dolby Atmos and Vision TV and audio system).

Anyone want to come over and watch it on a $12,000 AV system?

If you are a creator you are invited.

Do you know the way to San Jose? &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/applemusic/status/1421135999464210432&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 21:41:39 GMT" tweetId="1421224496330002434" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1421224496330002434" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="This isn’t about music.

It is about the creative process and innovation.

It will inspire many to create new experiences for others to enjoy.

Hugely important for the AR/VR industry.

It is life changing.

All six episodes are amazing. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/markronson/status/1421168458407071747&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 21:36:47 GMT" tweetId="1421223272197197827" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1421223272197197827" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Tim Cook watched Steve Jobs kick out Apple’s then current CEO. 

There is no way Tim will allow that to happen until he ships the things he worked for a decade on.

That is next year. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1421150913075503112&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 19:15:38 GMT" tweetId="1421187751383240706" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1421187751383240706" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="“Watch the Sound” with @MarkRonson is an amazing look at how tech is used in the music industry.

Must watch for people who care about experiences (either consuming or making). &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/markronson/status/1421168458407071747&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 18:42:20 GMT" tweetId="1421179370366898184" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1421179370366898184" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 29" type="calendarDay" name="29" >
				<outline text="I want Sutu’s Verse in my house. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/sutu_eats_flies/status/1420123521699569668&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 15:56:00 GMT" tweetId="1420775123569709060" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420775123569709060" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="My brain is a warehouse.

Full of boxes.

Some boxes are marked “keep away.”

I share those with you. Not voluntarily at first, but everyone did me a major gift.

Got me to see the value in having a crowd take a look.

Makes great friends.

Yes I will sign up for @neuralink" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 10:09:10 GMT" tweetId="1420687838027288578" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420687838027288578" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Almost always people feel guilty and then share their boxes with me" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 10:11:39 GMT" tweetId="1420688464878522373" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420688464878522373" inReplyToId="1420687838027288578" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
						<outline text="The conversation always leads to great places." type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 10:12:15 GMT" tweetId="1420688615697313794" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420688615697313794" inReplyToId="1420688464878522373" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="I expect to do most of this next Christmas. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/mashable/status/1420571529381773317&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 09:52:35 GMT" tweetId="1420683666217332741" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420683666217332741" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Where do toxic people come from?

Every time I take an asshole aside they were abused as children.

In my case my alcoholic mom participated in my sexual abuse.

Which is why I ask for empathy for assholes in the industry even as I agree they need to be removed and treated." type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 09:10:25 GMT" tweetId="1420673052862341121" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420673052862341121" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="I am physically shaking sharing this. I am getting through it with the help of @maryamie but this was my most painful tweet, by far." type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 09:16:14 GMT" tweetId="1420674519442759682" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420674519442759682" inReplyToId="1420673052862341121" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
						<outline text="The downside of #metoo" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 09:19:42 GMT" tweetId="1420675388204675080" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420675388204675080" inReplyToId="1420674519442759682" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 28" type="calendarDay" name="28" >
				<outline text="Now this looks interesting. The future is coming fast. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/metamaterialtec/status/1420189319260741633&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 19:08:49 GMT" tweetId="1420461256331333634" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420461256331333634" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Next Christmas our living rooms will look even better. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/sutu_eats_flies/status/1420410345974210560&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 19:06:35 GMT" tweetId="1420460697876451328" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420460697876451328" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="It might surprise you that I am for and support the #metoo movement. It is almost four years ago now.

Activision’s misdeeds has me writing tonight about why. I am an investor and I think investors have a huge role to play here. 

It is way past time for the industry to change." type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 09:10:06 GMT" tweetId="1420310585883824132" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420310585883824132" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="The CEO needs to go. Culture change is painful. But pain is how we learn and get better." type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 09:11:17 GMT" tweetId="1420310884962824197" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420310884962824197" inReplyToId="1420310585883824132" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
						<outline text="New management is needed. The old team has zero ability to credibly guide the company." type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 09:12:46 GMT" tweetId="1420311257584783361" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420311257584783361" inReplyToId="1420310884962824197" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
						</outline>
					<outline text="Once you remove yourself and start looking at the greater good you see the issues clearly." type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 09:30:58 GMT" tweetId="1420315835764076548" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420315835764076548" inReplyToId="1420310585883824132" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 27" type="calendarDay" name="27" >
				<outline text="Another magic of VR. @getsupernatural is awesome! It should be. Its founder was the first to show me Spatial Audio and VR. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brittlestar/status/1420027462793170946&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 22:34:21 GMT" tweetId="1420150594531053570" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420150594531053570" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="This is another place we all have gone down a bad path.

The best experiences will be done by diverse teams.

Beyoncé not fat white sexist guys like me.

Watch this of hers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jOSfoVdqSRk&amp;feature=youtu.be&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

This is the future. https://t.co/63oD35DSe1" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 22:25:49 GMT" tweetId="1420148448888688644" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420148448888688644" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Sutu is focusing on experiences. Brilliant. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/sutu_eats_flies/status/1420123521699569668&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 22:15:03 GMT" tweetId="1420145738449702916" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420145738449702916" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Look for Apple to accelerate over the next three years. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/neilcybart/status/1420121798117666820&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 22:11:53 GMT" tweetId="1420144940353351681" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420144940353351681" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="What I am looking forward to in VR/AR:

Going to a concert.
Taking a class.
Walking through photos.
Experiencing art museum.
Playing blackjack.
Traveling to places I can’t get to.

Focus on delivering experiences that blow people away. Or argue that this is all metaverse. :-)" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 21:57:04 GMT" tweetId="1420141212841832448" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420141212841832448" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="My 11-year-old son calls the Metaverse “playing with friends.”

He is on Discord and a variety of things that are technically the metaverse. They NEVER use the term metaverse.

It is where this industry has gone into a bad place.

Think about experiences." type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 18:54:38 GMT" tweetId="1420095299037499396" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1420095299037499396" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Metaverse is what you experience after doing LSD.

I stared at a brick wall for an hour once when I was tripping.

In the grout was an entire metaverse.

I hate the term already." type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 04:54:19 GMT" tweetId="1419883828143820800" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1419883828143820800" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="But if we are gonna use it @AeonixAeon should be on the board." type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 04:55:31 GMT" tweetId="1419884131370999811" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1419884131370999811" inReplyToId="1419883828143820800" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 26" type="calendarDay" name="26" >
				<outline text="Huge Spatial Audio/Dolby Atmos list of music. 

Way way way better sounding than Tidal or Spotify:

&lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/huge-spatial-audio-collection/pl.u-zJYsZ6806L&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 26 Jul 2021 21:50:02 GMT" tweetId="1419777053516197893" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1419777053516197893" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 23" type="calendarDay" name="23" >
				<outline text="I will use it. But I have almost my entire life there already.

That said there will be better. The kids aren’t doing anything on Facebook and they are in charge of which metaverse is worth visiting. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/karanganesan/status/1418215744739811331&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 23 Jul 2021 04:25:15 GMT" tweetId="1418426961253203969" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1418426961253203969" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 21" type="calendarDay" name="21" >
				<outline text="Why we have regulation… &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/urbanfoxxxx/status/1416350382217908224&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 17:25:09 GMT" tweetId="1417898455565967361" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1417898455565967361" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="If you have a Dolby Atmos surround sound audio system (Apple Max headphones are best here) @StevenWilsonHQ is a 3D audio pioneer: &lt;a href=&quot;https://music.apple.com/us/album/the-future-bites/1532089417&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 04:47:08 GMT" tweetId="1417707691397451776" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1417707691397451776" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 20" type="calendarDay" name="20" >
				<outline text="I have been to dozens of music festivals, Neil Young and his audio engineer has me listen to his masters (I have dozens of such stories, like seeing the Killers in someone’s back yard).

A $4,000 Dolby Atmos system from @sonos recreates 99.97% of that.

What is missing (thread):" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 21:03:52 GMT" tweetId="1417591108524134401" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1417591108524134401" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="1. The story. If you actually have the Killers in your backyard that is bragging rights for sure. Plus everyone who went talks about it for years. Powerful story." type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 21:03:52 GMT" tweetId="1417591109513924609" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1417591109513924609" inReplyToId="1417591108524134401" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
						<outline text="2. The smoothness of analog. The real world is analog. It is smooth and has more detail than you can reproduce yet at the $4,000 level. So going to a live concert will have some emotional magic you won’t get at home." type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 21:03:53 GMT" tweetId="1417591110638002178" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1417591110638002178" inReplyToId="1417591109513924609" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
							<outline text="3. The atmospherics and meaning they bring. I have seen major recording artists perform in vineyards and other cool places. With lifelong friends. We can deliver a lot of this digitally when we get mixed reality devices. Soon you will be able to visit my home virtually." type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 21:03:53 GMT" tweetId="1417591111413993472" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1417591111413993472" inReplyToId="1417591110638002178" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
								<outline text="In digital’s defense? It is a way nicer experience at home. Two trips to Coachella cost me $4,000. Now I can listen to anything and it sounds better because there isn’t another stage blasting 100-yards away. 

What does this mean for VR?

Apple’s device next year will match this." type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 21:03:53 GMT" tweetId="1417591112223498241" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1417591112223498241" inReplyToId="1417591111413993472" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
									<outline text="So everyone in the industry better learn how to do great audio. The competition will. I have seen it already. Every experience is mind-blowing. So you must match if you want to be relevant." type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 21:03:53 GMT" tweetId="1417591113011982339" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1417591113011982339" inReplyToId="1417591112223498241" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 16" type="calendarDay" name="16" >
				<outline text="I am hearing a lot of great things about @tiltfive’s latest game glasses, soon to ship. My kids can’t wait! My autistic son likes board games. Here is his collection with more in a closet. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Scobleizer/status/1416222308532817920/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 17 Jul 2021 02:24:45 GMT" tweetId="1416222308532817920" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1416222308532817920" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Innovation of the future. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/romainderrien/status/1416087529737134089&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 23:00:45 GMT" tweetId="1416170971862552583" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1416170971862552583" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Who knows most about what there is to watch on TV? 

1. The “code every minute programmer?”
2. The prolific artist?
3. The laid off “loser.”

Any losers wanna tell me what is up? My TV is hungry for 4K content. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Scobleizer/status/1416158701031878661/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 22:11:59 GMT" tweetId="1416158701031878661" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1416158701031878661" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="I am a loser, if you didn’t read USA Today. :-)" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 22:13:33 GMT" tweetId="1416159094138757123" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1416159094138757123" inReplyToId="1416158701031878661" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					<outline text="We will soon start a new media experience." type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 22:14:08 GMT" tweetId="1416159239484035074" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1416159239484035074" inReplyToId="1416158701031878661" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					<outline text="I learned this from family members, both employed and not." type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 22:43:00 GMT" tweetId="1416166503204806659" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1416166503204806659" inReplyToId="1416158701031878661" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Definitely sketchy. :-) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/appleinsider/status/1415776079214751748&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 18:11:14 GMT" tweetId="1416098111894605824" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1416098111894605824" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 15" type="calendarDay" name="15" >
				<outline text="Regarding Apple’s VR headset:

Just learned it will launch at WWDC next year because the new iPod will be a huge deal for Christmas.

The iPod introduces many of the experiences you will more fully experience by Christmas of 2022 in the headset and expect them to work together." type="tweet" created="Thu, 15 Jul 2021 05:54:10 GMT" tweetId="1415550236177559552" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1415550236177559552" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Consider anything I say about Apple as untrustworthy. But it is informed." type="tweet" created="Thu, 15 Jul 2021 06:03:36 GMT" tweetId="1415552608501047296" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1415552608501047296" inReplyToId="1415550236177559552" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 14" type="calendarDay" name="14" >
				<outline text="Just got my @LKGGlass 

I did not expect to be so blown away. 

@maryamie says “wow, that is cool.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Scobleizer/status/1415503080301350917/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 15 Jul 2021 02:46:47 GMT" tweetId="1415503080301350917" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1415503080301350917" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Everything I show you I buy. No freebies accepted." type="tweet" created="Thu, 15 Jul 2021 02:47:30 GMT" tweetId="1415503259926630402" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1415503259926630402" inReplyToId="1415503080301350917" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Another taste of the future. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jarlanperez/status/1414681140577935363&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 15 Jul 2021 01:15:43 GMT" tweetId="1415480161185632257" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1415480161185632257" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 11" type="calendarDay" name="11" >
				<outline text="There is a club. The only requirement for membership is that you need to want better experiences. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/surrealcalarco/status/1414073605571371010&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 04:08:48 GMT" tweetId="1414074168115535876" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1414074168115535876" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 10" type="calendarDay" name="10" >
				<outline text="If I had a time machine I would go back to when my mom was yelling at me to sit away from the TV.

But first I would get my @MojoVisionInc’s contact lens which puts a TV onto the surface of your eyes.

This is why I can’t stand audio purists who say Spatial Audio is evil." type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 03:41:00 GMT" tweetId="1414067172196765698" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1414067172196765698" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="My ears LOVE Spatial Audio from Apple." type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 03:45:57 GMT" tweetId="1414068416076410886" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1414068416076410886" inReplyToId="1414067172196765698" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Yoke haters are wrong. Sat in a Plaid today. Stuff that made no sense last year." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 05:35:21 GMT" tweetId="1413733563048947716" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1413733563048947716" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 9" type="calendarDay" name="09" >
				<outline text="I had a dream that I was at SpaceX and took a photo of a firetruck.

Dream achieved.

I made up the part about the firetruck. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Scobleizer/status/1413696841674215426/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 03:09:26 GMT" tweetId="1413696841674215426" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1413696841674215426" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 6" type="calendarDay" name="06" >
				<outline text="It wasn't just the camera that doomed it. Fun report on what happened to Google Glass. &lt;a href=&quot;https://video.foxnews.com/v/6262482235001&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 19:58:21 GMT" tweetId="1412501189669777410" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1412501189669777410" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Apple's Spatial Audio is not understood by most of the market yet, my research shows. I'm convinced that they only wanted nerds like me to know about it. Most people don't use Apple Music. Most people also don't have the audio equipment to properly hear it. 

That will change." type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 19:35:19 GMT" tweetId="1412495392994840578" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1412495392994840578" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Apple is about to launch a new iPod, which will do a new version of Spatial Audio, that will push Apple way ahead of Spotify and Tidal in audio quality. 

No one will be able to catch up until they figure out how to put AI capabilities into a mesh network in your home." type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 19:35:19 GMT" tweetId="1412495393879855104" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1412495393879855104" inReplyToId="1412495392994840578" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
						<outline text="Spatial Audio plays best on M1 Macs that have a lot of AI capabilities. Apple uses those capabilities to make the sound better. Soon a LOT better because Apple will start locking audio to the real world to prepare for its VR device, which I call the Holodeck, coming next year." type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 19:35:19 GMT" tweetId="1412495394764845058" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1412495394764845058" inReplyToId="1412495393879855104" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
							<outline text="It is also amazing the resistance my research found, to pushing people into Apple's ecosystem. Most refuse to even give Apple a serious listen to see the difference. It's amazing the resistance people give to something that legitimately is a lot better." type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 19:37:20 GMT" tweetId="1412495903051583488" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1412495903051583488" inReplyToId="1412495394764845058" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Rats in VR? Yes! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/BrennanSpiegel/status/1412493387060584451&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 19:28:33 GMT" tweetId="1412493689524428802" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1412493689524428802" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="My Airtags have survived two washings. Shower photo next? :-)" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 07:03:41 GMT" tweetId="1412306240567353362" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1412306240567353362" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="June 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="june2021" >
			<outline text="June 28" type="calendarDay" name="28" >
				<outline text="I have had MANY arguments with experts over decades. They are usually wrong when going through intense change. Only arguing with lawyers is harder. But must be done. 

Every time we go into a new era they argue with me. Where is Wordperfect? The “experts” said it was best." type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 23:51:37 GMT" tweetId="1409660789976227840" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1409660789976227840" tweetUserName="scobleizer" >
					<outline text="Now I am arguing with experts in the audio industry. Such arrogance." type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 23:52:12 GMT" tweetId="1409660938811109377" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1409660938811109377" inReplyToId="1409660789976227840" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 25" type="calendarDay" name="25" >
				<outline text="Playing Spatial Audio off of an M1-based Apple Mac sounds way better than using the latest Apple TV.

Here is the kicker: this is true of you Airplay to that same Apple TV.

If you want the best sound you have to play around." type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:07:21 GMT" tweetId="1408456790983905281" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1408456790983905281" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Did you know billionaires have 12K screens and pay up to $500 to watch a cinema-release of a movie? (One I was talking to has a theater in their new home. A bunch called about my lights).

Next year Apple’s “Holodeck” (my made-up name for its VR headset) will be way better. https://t.co/AVDJsEFo3l" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 10:31:19 GMT" tweetId="1408372225569263618" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1408372225569263618" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		</body>
